== Zesty Kiwi Salsa ==

Peel the @kiwi{1}, then cut into 1cm chunks. Halve the @red chilli{1} lengthways, deseed, then finely chop.

Trim and thinly slice the @spring onion{1}. Zest and halve the @lime{1}.

Pop the kiwi, chilli (add less if you'd prefer things milder) and spring onion into a #medium bowl{}. Squeeze in the lime juice and @olive oil{} for the salsa. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}, mix together, then set aside.

== Green Beans ==

Trim and halve the @green beans{80%g}. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once the pan is hot, add the green beans and stir-fry until starting to char, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in the garlic, then turn the heat down to medium and cook for ~{1%minute}. Add a splash of @water{} and immediately cover with a #lid{} or some #foil{}. Cook until the beans are tender, ~{4-5%minutes}. Remove the pan from the heat.

Pop the green beans into a #bowl{} and cover with foil to keep warm.

== Jasmine Rice ==

Pour the @water{300%ml} for the rice into a #medium saucepan{} with a tight-fitting lid.

Stir in the @jasmine rice{150%g} and @salt{1/4%tsp} and bring to the boil. Once boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

== Teriyaki Prawns ==

Return the (now empty) pan to a medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{}. Drain the @king prawns{300%g} and pat dry with #kitchen paper{}.

Once hot, add the prawns to the pan. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{} and cook for ~{4-5%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw prawns. They're cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.

Meanwhile, crush the @salted peanuts{25%g} in the unopened sachet using a #rolling pin{}.

Once the prawns are cooked, remove the pan from the heat and pour in the @teriyaki sauce{75%ml}.

Gently toss to combine and coat the prawns in the sauce.

== Assembly ==

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and stir through the lime zest.

Share the rice between your #bowls{}, then serve the teriyaki prawns, kiwi salsa (including the juices) and green beans in separate sections on top.

Sprinkle over the crushed peanuts to finish. Enjoy!